      "id": "daily_organization",
      "title": "Daily Organization & Pedagogical Loop",
      "content": "# Daily Organization & Pedagogical Loop\n\nTo succeed at the Symfony 8.0 Certification, consistency is far more important than intensity. Trying to cram documentation on weekends will lead to burnout and forgotten concepts. Instead, follow this structured, **high-retention daily loop**.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udcc5 The 1-Hour Daily Loop\n\nYour golden standard is **1 hour per day**, 5 days a week. For each topic (e.g., `Routing`, `Dependency Injection`), follow this exact sequence:\n\n### 1. \ud83d\udcd6 Theory & Reading (25 mins)\nStart by opening a Topic in the **Course Player**. \nRead through the documentation extract. This phase is purely about understanding the mechanics. \n> **Action:** Use the *Personal Notebook* panel to write down your own mnemonics or specific tricky constraints you discover (e.g., \"Services are private by default\").\n\n### 2. \u26a1 Flashcards & Spaced Repetition (10 mins)\nOnce you have read the theory, click the **Practice Flashcards** button.\nThese flashcards contain the core *must-know* facts without the fluff.\n> **Action:** Read the question. Try to formulate the exact answer in your head *before* flipping the card. If you got it wrong, review the code snippet provided on the back of the card.\n\n### 3. \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Practice & Code Review (10 mins)\nTheory easily evaporates if not applied. You do not need to write entire applications every day, but you *must* read code.\n> **Action:** Open your local editor and review one of the bug exercises in the `code-reviews/` folder related to your current topic. Or, write a tiny reproducible script in `public/index.php` to test a feature you just read about.\n\n### 4. \ud83c\udfaf Quiz Validation (15 mins)\nThe exam format is very specific (True/False and Multiple Choice). You must train your brain to spot trick questions and exact syntax requirements.\n> **Action:** Click the **Take Exam** button for your current topic. Do not guess blindly. If you are unsure, flag the topic for review and re-read the documentation. \n> **Goal:** You must achieve an 85% passing score to comfortably move to the next lesson.\n\n---\n\n## \u267b\ufe0f The Weekend Review\n\nDo not study new sub-topics on the weekend. The weekend is strictly reserved for consolidating knowledge:\n1. **Mindmap Sweep:** Open the Roadmap Mindmap and click **[\u26a1 Flashcards]** strictly for the topics you studied *this week*.\n2. **Mock Exams:** Try answering random questions from the global pool horizontally, cross-referencing different components.\n\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> **Trust the Process:** By forcing your brain to Retrieve (Flashcards) and Evaluate (Quizzes) immediately after Reading (Theory), you guarantee long-term retention. \n"
